quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  12,80,"So when they despaired of him they went apart conferring secretly. The eldest of them said, “Do you not know that your father had taken an undertaking from you in (the name of) Allah, and earlier (too) you failed (in keeping up your undertaking) in the case of Yusuf. Therefore I will not leave this land till my father permits me or Allah decides (something) for me and He is the Best of judges"
  12,81,"Return to your father and say: O our father ! your son committed theft and we do not bear witness except regarding that which we know and we could not be protectors of the unseen"
  12,82,"And inquire in the city in which we were, and (also from) the caravan with which we travelled and we are certainly truthful.”"
  12,83,"He (Yaqub) said, “No ! your souls have induced this affair for you so patience is good. May be Allah will bring them all together to me, He is certainly the Knowing, the Wise.”"
  12,84,"And he turned away from them and said, “O my sorrow for Yusuf,” and his eyes became white due to grief but he suppressed"
  12,85,"They said, “By Allah ! you will not cease to remember Yusuf till your health is ruined or you become one of those who perish.”"
  12,86,"He said, “I expose my distress and grief only to Allah and I know from Allah that which you do not know"
  12,87,"O my sons ! go and inquire about Yusuf and his brother and do not despair of the mercy of Allah, no one despairs of the mercy of Allah except the people who are infidels.”"
  12,88,"So when they entered in his (Yusuf’s) presence, they said, “O you who are mighty ! harm has afflicted us and our people and we have brought poor merchandise, so give us full measure (of provision) and be charitable to us, Allah certainly rewards the charitable.”"
  12,89,"He said, “Do you know what you did with Yusuf and his brother while you were ignorant.”"
  12,90,"They said, “You ! are you indeed Yusuf ?” He said, “I am Yusuf and this is my brother, Allah has indeed been gracious to us; (for) him who guards (against evil) and is patient, Allah certainly does not waste the reward of the doers of good.”"
  12,91,"They said, “By Allah, Allah has indeed preferred you above us and indeed we were at fault.”"
  12,92,"He said, “Let there be no reproach on you this day. May Allah protectively forgive you and He is the Most Merciful of the merciful ones"
  12,93,"Go with this shirt of mine and put it on the face of my father, (his power of) seeing will come (back to him) and come to me with all your people.”"